AI Career Hub — Alembic Migration Directory
============================================

This directory is managed by Alembic (https://alembic.sqlalchemy.org).

Files
-----
  env.py            — Migration environment: loads settings, Base, and runs
                      offline or online migrations.
  script.py.mako    — Template used to generate new migration files.
  versions/         — Auto-generated migration scripts.  Do not rename or
                      reorder files manually; Alembic tracks history by
                      revision ID chains, not filename order.

Quick Reference (run from backend/)
------------------------------------
  Generate a migration (after editing models):
      .\\venv\\Scripts\\alembic revision --autogenerate -m "describe change"

  Apply all pending migrations:
      .\\venv\\Scripts\\alembic upgrade head

  Roll back one step:
      .\\venv\\Scripts\\alembic downgrade -1

  View current revision:
      .\\venv\\Scripts\\alembic current

  View full history:
      .\\venv\\Scripts\\alembic history --verbose

  Generate offline SQL (no live DB required):
      .\\venv\\Scripts\\alembic upgrade head --sql > migration.sql

Adding a New Model
------------------
1. Create  backend/app/models/my_model.py
2. Define  class MyModel(Base): ...
3. Register in backend/app/db/base.py:
       from app.models.my_model import MyModel  # noqa: F401
4. Generate the migration:
       .\\venv\\Scripts\\alembic revision --autogenerate -m "add my_model table"
5. Review the generated file in versions/ before applying.
6. Apply:
       .\\venv\\Scripts\\alembic upgrade head